# Multicopter Attitude & Rate Control — Per-Channel Architecture Map

## Context

This document maps the rate and attitude control loops as they exist in **your** PX4-Autopilot fork on branch `hotfix` (HEAD `791030d7`). It traces signals end-to-end per axis (roll, pitch, yaw), names the parameters, gives the exact control equations from your source, and flags the places where this fork differs from upstream PX4. Use it as a reference for tuning, debugging, and as the foundation for the SysID work tracked elsewhere.

---

## High-level cascade

```
                  ┌──────────────────────── stabilized / position mode
                  │
   sticks ───► generate_attitude_setpoint() ──► vehicle_attitude_setpoint.q_d
                                                          │
                                                          ▼
   vehicle_attitude.q ─────────────────────► AttitudeControl::update(q, rates)
                                                          │  rate_setpoint = P·eq − D·rates + ψ_FF
                                                          ▼
                                              vehicle_rates_setpoint.{roll,pitch,yaw}
                  ┌──────────────────────── acro mode (sticks → rates directly)
                  │
                  ▼
   vehicle_angular_velocity.{xyz, xyz_derivative} ─► RateControl::update(rate, rate_sp, accel, dt, landed)
                                                          │  τ = K·[P·(rate_sp−rate) + ∫ − D·accel + FF·rate_sp]
                                                          ▼
                                              vehicle_torque_setpoint.xyz[3]      (and vehicle_thrust_setpoint)
                                                          │
                                                          ▼
                                              ControlAllocator ──► actuator_motors.control[0..N]
```

